                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3b85441p/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>New York</placeName>, <date>October 3,\n                1864</date>.</p>\n            <p><addressee>Reverend Isaac Leeser</addressee>,\n                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>,</p>\n            <p>Honored Sir:</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Herewith a draft for $21. for the holiday prayer books<lb/> in\n                ordinary binding, and send me by return a set of holiday prayer<lb/> books for $21.\n                and a set of gilt. And if you have no gilded ones,<lb/> then send me a set for\n                $25.50., as <sic>wellas</sic> several Portuguese prayer<lb/> books. I live opposite\n                the new Portuguese synagogue.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">You may also send me a large set (I mean large octavo) in<lb/> gilt,\n                if you have no small ones.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(9)\">Respectfully,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(10)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">M. Light</persName>\n            </p>\n            <p>I have received Italian ethrogim, and I sell them wholesale or retail.<lb/> Perhaps\n                you will be able to sell several boxes for me, if only several<lb/> ethrogim for\n                your congregation. Send me....(German note about sub-<lb/>scribers to\n                “Occident”).</p>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3b85441p/canvas/p3"
